N2  - The article presents a comment on an article from a previous issue titled ? Technology and Organization Government,? by William G. Scott. The author takes issue with Scott's claim that an organization adopts a creed and works within that construct. Instead, he argues that his organization uses elements of several creeds in order to achieve their management goals. The author argues that organizations that permit managers to gain personal power by using the organization to achieve that end will have to change.
